===========
Description
===========

This is a cubic B-spline editor with extra features panning, zooming, 

adaptive parameterization, anti-aliasing, and control poly-line toggling.

===========
Compilation
===========

"make" gives the program "editSpline"

"make clean" removes the intermediate files generated during compilation.

=====
Usage
=====

------------
Command Line
------------

./editSpline (xRes) (yRes)

For example:

./editSpline 500 500

----------
Parameters
----------

xRes            The width of the window. Must be a positive integer.

yRes            The height of the window. Must be a positive integer.

==============
User Interface
==============

----------------
Mouse Operations
----------------

Left-click & Drag            Move a control point

Right-click                  Insert a knot

Shift + Left-click & Drag    Pan the camera

--------------
Key Operations
--------------

Esc/Q   Quit the program

C       Toggle display and editing of the control poly-line

I       Zoom in w.r.t center of image

O       Zoom out w.r.t center of image

R       Restore the initial view

